<section id="expectations" class="slide">
  <h2>Expectations</h2>
  <p>
    For checking the expectations, <strong>expect(obj).to</strong> and <strong>expect(obj).not_to</strong> methods are used.
  </p>
  <h3>Checking equality and identity</h3>
  Equality
  <script type="syntaxhighlighter" class="brush: ruby">
    expect(cow).to eq(twin_cow)
  </script>
  Identity
  <script type="syntaxhighlighter" class="brush: ruby">
    expect(cow).to equal(twin_cow)
  </script>
  <p>
    The <strong>eq</strong> methods are used to express values equivalence, and <strong>equal</strong> are used when you want the receiver and the argument to be the same object.
  </p>
</section>